If $x \equiv 4 \pmod{19}$ and $y \equiv 7 \pmod{19}$, then find the remainder when $(x + 1)^2 (y + 5)^3$ is divided by 19.
inference:
$x \equiv 4 \pmod{19}$, $y \equiv 7 \pmod{19}$
$(x+1)^2 (y+5)^3$
$x+1 \equiv 4+1 \equiv 5 \pmod{19}$
$y+5 \equiv 7+5 \equiv 12 \pmod{19}$
$(x+1)^2 \equiv 5^2 \equiv 25 \equiv 6 \pmod{19}$
$(y+5)^3 \equiv 12^3 \equiv 1728 \pmod{19}$
$1728 = 19 \times 91 + 19$
$1728 = 91 \times 19 + 9 \times 19$
$1728 \equiv 9 \pmod{19}$
$(x+1)^2(y+5)^3 \equiv 6 \times 9 \equiv 54 \equiv 17 \pmod{19}$
Final Answer: $\boxed{17}$ I hope it is correct.
